rComments: Great professor. Gives good feedback during critiques and really works with students to develop their ideas. Interesting lectures which provide insight on real life architecture in big firms.

Very understanding, and usually unlike other professors who like to demean, and put their students down, he is really kind and even his style of critiquing students is done through a nice way. He provides extensive feedback, I have never seen another professor who instead of imposing actually tries to understand why the student did what he/she did.
BEST PROFESSOR I'VE HAD FROM DANIELS & very motivational :)

Professor Jon paid attention to little details and gave very constructive feedback for next projects. You can tell he genuinely cares about his students. He goes out of his way to help us with the projects and more importantly when he teaches, it allows us to view things from a different perspective.
He doesn't give much feedback for the work, and not willing to listen for your ideas, kind of unrespectful, better not to be in his class

Average prof. Clear critique with suggestions for future improvement every time (which I appreciate) but change his words very often. You will have to forget about his technical approach to architecture and urbanism as you move to 300 level studios because by then everything's pretty conceptual and less in his way (his approach suits firms though)

Jon was my studio prof this semester. He was great, helped me and my classmates along with our projects and gave awesome feedback to improve. He also gave advice on finding summer jobs in firms and took a look at our portfolios, which he really didn't have to do. I really hope I have him in the future. (Side note: tutorials are useless, don't go!)
